message.raw:
Added brute_import, which contains a function that allows inspecting of a module
that has failed to import. This can be useful for diagnosing why it failed
to import and providing potentially more useful error messages.

Modified check_version to use brute_import in the case of a module
failing to import, so that the version may still be checked in the case of a
failed import. This helps determine whether the failed import was due
to a version mismatch or to something else.

Merged in cbillington/labscript_utils/feature2 (pull request #14)

Make analog output widgets not steal focus on scrolling

Approved-by: Shaun Johnstone <shaun.johnstone@monash.edu>
Approved-by: Philip Starkey <philip.starkey@monash.edu>

message.raw:
Subclassed QDoubleSpinBox for use with analog output widgets so that they
don't steal focus when you scroll over them. You can still scroll on them to
change their value if they've been focused by a mouse click or tab, but
scrolling over them will not focus them, and scrolling elsewhere whilst they
are focused will cause them to lose focus, so you can scroll with confidence.
